leadership_approach|process_results_people_vision|paired|process|results|people|vision|A reliable route through the work|Your leadership approach is led by Process and strengthened by Results. You tend to create confidence by giving work a clearer route, then making sure that route produces practical movement. People and Vision also matter, but they usually need to be brought in deliberately before the plan becomes too fixed.|The paired shape means Process and Results should be read together. This is not structure for its own sake, and it is not delivery pursued chaotically. Your strongest pattern is method used in service of dependable progress.|You lead first by making work clearer, more sequenced, and easier to hold together.|Results gives that structure a practical edge, keeping the plan connected to decisions, movement, and visible progress.|People adds range by helping the route become shared, trusted, and owned by the team rather than only understood.|Vision adds range when you connect the immediate route to a larger direction, purpose, and future capability.|review|leadership_approach::process_results_people_vision::paired
